approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

decimals().details: Decimals are computed by adding the decimal offset on top of the underlying asset's decimals. This "original" value is cached during construction of the vault contract. If this read operation fails (e.g., the asset has not been created yet), a default of 18 is used to represent the underlying asset's decimals. See {IERC20Metadata-decimals}.

returns._0: liquidToken Address of the token received from the deployment strategy.
returns._1: liquidTokenAmount Amount of the liquid token received.

params.account_: Address of the account on behalf of which the tokens are deposited.

returns._0: sharesAmount Amount of shares issued for the deposited assets.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

returns._0: vaultValuation Current valuation of the vault, including deployed assets and pending deposits.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

returns._0: token Address of the token received from the harvest.
returns._1: tokenAmount Amount of the token received.

params.ownerAddress_: Address of the vault's owner who will receive the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE.
params.sharesName_: Name for the ERC20 shares token.
params.sharesSymbol_: Symbol for the ERC20 shares token.
params.underlyingTokenAddress_: ERC20 token that the vault will accept as deposits.

mint(uint256,address).details: Reverts any call to mint to prevent bypassing the deposit logic.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

params.account_: Address of the account receiving the assets.
params.caller_: Address representing the master token invoking the redemption.

returns._0: assetsAmount Amount of assets received for the redeemed shares.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.status_: True for enabling live valuation, false to disable.
params.target_: Target operation, 0 for deposit and 1 for withdrawal.

params.valuationSource_: The number indicating the valuation source

params.vaultStrategyAddress_: The new strategy address for asset allocation.

params.withdrawStrategyAddress_: The new strategy address for handling withdrawals.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

params.priceSource_: Specifies from where to get the price when no oracle is defined

returns._0: vaultValuation Updated valuation of the vault.

params.account_: Address of the account from which shares are burned.
params.caller_: Address representing the master token invoking the withdrawal.

returns._0: sharesAmount Amount of shares burned to perform the withdrawal.

MASTER_TOKEN_ROLE().notice: Role to identify master token operations.

REVERT_MSG().notice: Message to revert when an operation is not allowed.

VAULT_MANAGER_ROLE().notice: Role identifier for addresses that can manage vault operations.

deployAssets().notice: Deploys assets according to the defined strategy for asset management.

deposit(uint256,address).notice: Allows assets to be deposited in exchange for shares, adhering to access controls.

getVaultValuation().notice: Retrieves the current valuation of the vault.

harvest().notice: Harvests earnings from the strategy, adhering to access controls.

initialize(address,address,address,addre.notice: Initializes the vault with necessary configurations and roles.

liveValuationOnDeposit().notice: Indicates if live valuation is performed during deposits.

liveValuationOnWithdraw().notice: Indicates if live valuation is performed during withdrawals.

masterTokenAddress().notice: Address of the master token contract associated with the vault.

mint(uint256,address).notice: Overrides the mint function to disable direct minting of shares.

pause().notice: Pauses the vault's operations, preventing any state-changing functions.

pendingDepositAssets().notice: Total amount of assets pending deposit before harvest.

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: Redeems shares for underlying assets, adhering to access controls.

setLiveValuation(bool,uint256).notice: Sets whether to perform live valuation during deposit or withdrawal.

setMasterTokenAddress(address).notice: Sets the address of the master token.

setValuationSource(uint8).notice: Sets the valuationSource to tell the contract where to get prices where oracle is not definedvaluationSource_ = 1 take price from deposit adaptervaluationSource_ = 2 take price from withdraw adapter

setVaultStrategyAddress(address).notice: Sets the address of the vault strategy.

setVaultsRegistryAddress(address).notice: Sets the address of the vaults registry.

setWithdrawStrategyAddress(address).notice: Sets the address of the withdrawal strategy.

unpause().notice: Unpauses the vault's operations, allowing state-changing functions.

updateVaultValuation(uint8).notice: Updates the vault's valuation based on the current asset deployment.

valuationSource().notice: Indicates from where (deposit/withdraw adapter) to valuate vault when oracle is not present1 is deposit , 2 is withdraw

vaultsRegistryAddress().notice: Address of the registry contract that keeps track of all vaults.

withdraw(uint256,address,address).notice: Allows the withdrawal of assets in exchange for burning shares, adhering to access controls.

withdrawStrategyAddress().notice: Address of the strategy used for handling withdrawals.When using immediate withdraw this will match vaultStrategyAddress
